me—aims at returning to and revitalizing the past so as to make possible a dynamic-embodied present and a future pregnant with change. Söderbäck stages an unprecedented conversation between Kristeva and Irigaray on issues of both time and difference, and engages thinkers such as Simone de Beauvoir, Jacques Derrida, Sigmund Freud, Judith Butler, Hannah Arendt, and Plato along the way.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aFeminist theory. 0aSex differences. 0aTime. 4aGender and Sexuality : Feminist. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Feminist Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2019z978311149143140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847701540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438477015423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438477015/original  a978-3-11-149143-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles